Some basic, simple modules

pull_request.title: Some basic, simple modules
pull_request.body:
A first series of six modules, tested and usable, along with doc, source files, data, and pictures/screenshots. This set of module `CFG-arduino_servo`, can be used on its own, or in conjunction with other modules, based on the overall, common motherboard tracks.
Aim of this module isn't to get high-quality, high-framerate images, rather to provide with a basic toolset to work with ultrasound.

comment.body:
The idea in this push is to provide the echopen community with simplified, preassembled boards, so that the community can use easy-to-use, lower-cost boards, that have been thourougly tested - or to order some from their fabs/fablabs/... . To be noted, the redpitaya is replaced by a cheaper wifi-enable arduino that streams data over udp, and still gives relatively [good images](https://github.com/kelu124/echomods/blob/master/croaker/data/20161217/20161217-TestingArduinoAndPhantom.md).

Some of these modules are used (in the [original repo](https://github.com/kelu124/echomods/)), some in academic /  private projects, and subject of a [publication](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.10174) - these projects, as forks of the original project, naturally keep their rights and licenses.

However, on this subset of modules, I allow this fork to use the [echopen license](https://github.com/echopen/PRJ-medtec_kit/blob/99b4b9a72d0b468ce858072ed32b017d0ac2790a/license/echopen_general_public_licence_20150915.wiki), which grants the echopen project a license to use this contribution as per its license terms: "Each contributor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free patent license under the contributor's essential patent claims, to make, use, sell, offer for sale, import and otherwise run, modify and propagate the contents of its contributor version. " - in short, the community can use this contribution as it wishes =)
